KANO – Kano was thrown into mourning on Friday as four female teenagers and a 32-year old woman lost their lives at an excavation site in Dauni village, Minjibir Local Government Area of the state. Malam Sai’idu Mohammed, spokesman, Kano State Fire Service at a session with reporters named the victims to include Sa’ida Lawwali (32); Dije Shu’aibu (8); Hadiza Shu’aibu (12;) Nana Idris (12) and Wasila Nuhu (13). Mohammed also confirmed that a four-year old boy, Ibrahim Shuaibu was rescued alongside six other toddlers from the site. According to him, most of the survivors sustained multiple fractures adding that they were taken to an unnamed government hospital for medical attention. He revealed that the tragic incident occurred last Thursday at about 2.45 pm at Ramin Farar Kasa in the village when the victims were digging white sand used for make-up powder. He said: “We received a distress call on Thursday afternoon from Dauni village through one Malam Danlami Murtala at about 02:45 pm that a heap of sand has trapped six people, who were digging sand. “Upon receiving the information, we quickly dispatched our firemen and a fire engine to the scene of the incident. We made frantic efforts to rescue the victims but we were only able to successfully rescue the little boy of about four years old, who was found alive.” He said bodies of the victims were handed over to the village head of Dauni, Alhaji Bello Rabi’u for burial rights.